            <p>Richard Gregory, a professor of neuropsychology at Bristol University, was having coffee at a local café when he noticed that the tiles on the wall looked highly distorted and sloped. He went back to his lab, reconstructed the pattern, and published the classic "Café Wall" paper.</p>
